ENTRY            C0959   20260324   20260518   20260518       C257
SUBENT        C0959001   20260324   20260518   20260518       C257
BIB                 12         53
TITLE      Production of A=6,7 nuclides in the alpha+alpha
           reaction and cosmic ray nucleosynthesis
AUTHOR     (D.J.Mercer,S.M.Austin,J.A.Brown,S.A.Danczyk,
           S.E.Hirzebruch,J.H.Kelley,T.Suomijarvi,D.A.Roberts,
           T.P.Walker)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,63,065805,2001)
           #doi:10.1103/PhysRevC.63.065805
           (J,NP/A,688,70,2001) Conference proceedings.
           #doi:10.1016/S0375-9474(01)00671-6
INSTITUTE  (1USACLU,1USAMSU,2FR PAR,1USAMHG,1USAOSU)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,1USAMSU) NSCL
INC-SPECT  Beams of alpha particles were provided by the NSCL
           K1200 Cyclotron at nominal energies of 160, 280, and
           620 MeV. The lowest energy was chosen to allow direct
           comparison with previous results, and the higher
           energies were chosen to span the region of
           astrophysical interest. All beams were fully stripped
           upon arrival at the scattering chamber. Up to 1.2 MeV
           is deposited in the entrance foil and target gas
           prior to the reaction, depending on the initial
           energy and point of scatter. The average bombarding
           energies, accounting for these losses and the 0.2 MeV
           uncertainty in the measured energy, were 159.36+-0.5
           MeV, 279.66+-0.4 MeV, and 619.86+-0.3 MeV.
DETECTOR   (TELES) 2 detector telescopes, each consisting of a
            stack of position-sensitive silicon detectors and
            one CsI(Tl) scintillator.
SAMPLE     Natural helium gas at 23 degrees C in cylinder with
            Havar window. Gas pressure 370-408 Torr.
METHOD     (EDE)
ADD-RES    (TRCS) Total cross sections (mb) for 2-HE-4(A,X) for
           production of 6He+6Li (g.s.+3.56)
           -------------------------------------------------------
           EN         EN-ERR     DATA       DATA-ERR
           MEV        MEV        MB         MB
           159.3       0.05        5.3        0.4
           279.6        0.4       0.64       0.08
           619.7        0.3      0.015      0.004
           -------------------------------------------------------
           Total cross section (mb) for 2-HE-4(A,X) for
           production of 7Li (g.s.+0.48)+7Be (g.s.+0.43)
           -------------------------------------------------------
           EN         EN-ERR     DATA       DATA-ERR   DATA-MAX
           MEV        MEV        MB         MB         MB
           159.3       0.05       1.87       0.17
           279.6        0.4      0.050      0.017
           619.7        0.3                            0.006
           -------------------------------------------------------
STATUS     (APRVD) Approved by D. Mercer, 25 March 2004.
HISTORY    (20040123C) VM
           (20260324A) BP: Added ADD-RES to cover the duplicate
           entry C2373, additional REFERENCE,DOI, updated STATUS,
           fixed spelling errors in TITLE and DETECTOR.
ENDBIB              53
